caption: I'm a sucker for deep fried sushi rolls, and the Capitol Roll is so simple but so delicious. I'm happy to work this into my regular rotation.
Love their sushi
Great location with cozy interior, good touch less system and great service. Food is delicious and a good spot for date night. Been here a few times already.
The chirashi bowl and the prime beef nigiri were perfect, and the ordering system was great as well as the ambience

The sushi was ok. Nothing special. We were really disappointed by the tomato/pepper relish that was inexplicably dumped on top of our yellowtail and scallion roll. It wasn't in the description. We absolutelywould not have ordered that if we had known.
Loved it!  Great food and great atmosphere
A bit on the pricey side, but great mushroom sushi with onion jam.

Service was wonderful from start to finish and the fish itself is very fresh. While it may not be the most impressive sushi in DC, it's definitely up there and for the price point alone, may be hard to beat. To find quality fish at a reasonable price isn't easy and I think Sushi Hachi has figured out that balance
Great vibe. Great sushie. I loved the crunchy shrimp roll. They were small though,  but I'll be back.  The udon noodles were not as great though. I thought it was not as tasty and small.

CJ...thankyou sweetheart you did well to make the experience much better than expected 💗, this was my first time here and I was pretty happy with most items and the only reason for 4 stars was because of the deep fried roll was Half Burnt 🥶😵😫 and Rice was not seasoned well but I will be coming back this week or next and I would say for everyone else to definitely give this place a try because they do have many items on and off menu that you need to try out , so if you are in this area of Washington DC stop by Sushi 🍣 Hachi and Check out the Music, Club/Lounge like ambiance, special items and fast friendly service.
Great sushi and environment. I also like the menu and payment system they use.

Worst customer service ever.... period... rushed, rude and unprofessional... “We have other orders but yours you know, you aren’t the only one so you’ll have to wait more then 2 hours” Me: How long? “I don’t know, maybe more , I have other customers”... and so on. I tried ordering at 5:30 and they wanted to get the food ready at or around 9pm... Manager he said was Ken and he’s the one I had conversation with. I don’t know if I can believe he was the “manager or not” owner needs to hear it because they just lost a $300 order... never ordering..
Top notch. Great ambiance, great sushi!
Very nice little spot. Food is tasty and servers are friendly and eager to give recommendations.

This place is the one I always prefer. I visit many restaurants but to this one I  constantly return again and again. The team is very helpful and the cuisine they place on your table is so yummy. I would always prefer to have a nice meal in this restaurant. I highly recommend this place.
Delightful

The food was great but I was disappointed when we ordered our food from Grubhub. All the sushi in one of our containers were flipped over. It may had been the drivers fault or the chef could have used a smaller container so that the sushi won’t roll over. We called the restaurant to let them know about the food but we have not heard back yet. Our order also took about an hour and 15 min to get it delivered. But again, there’s no problem with the food and Sushi Hachi has good quality sushi.

This restaurant is my favorite. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The team is very affectionate and the food they cook is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.
Incredibly tasty sushi that is on par with or better than anything you'll find in LA or NYC! Get Hachi's Churashi Sushi - downright delightful, fresh fish, and a steal for $25.
Best place in town. Highly recommend
Online and in store ordering. Contactless pickup. Great food.
This has got to be the best sushi place in town,the food is great and the service is the best ever. Highly recommend.
Nice place. Food is good but wish they had more variety of sushi.
Sushi was bland and overpriced. Very disappointed as it has such nice reviews
Great staff and wonderful food

I’ve always ordered from this place on DoorDash or Uber eats and finally I was able to stop in and have an experience in the flesh if you will! First of all, the decor, stellar! I really enjoyed the little mini hand towel at the table that puffs up after it’s soaked in water! Nice touch. I LOVE THEIR VEGETABLE TEMPURA!!!!! A MUST!!! Great to start with and then just dive in!  Try the Alaska roll. Thank me later
Amazing sushi Great drinks and completely contactless
Food is okay. Maybe my expectations were too high. Service is good. I wish google had half stars..
It’s my first time to dine here, & the food, ambiance is very cool & service is great! Feels like  japan! lol but Our server “Z” he’s amazing! So definitely recommend the place & will come back too!
This place is amazing, great food, great ambiance, great customer service and very affordable!!

My wife and I couldn't believe how we had to choose for a tip before the service was even rendered. The food, drinks, and ambiance was fabulous, but the customer service was horrible at least to us. They need a true introduction to consistency with greeting and engaging with their customers.
Great food, drinks and ambiance, but poor service, leaving a tip for a service you haven't been offered is not okay.
GREAT HOT FOOD👅👅👅👅👅
Good sushi, great service. Have nice patio seating open.
Fantastic veggie tempura! They have taken the simple things like miso soup, California rolls and house salad and made them divine!
Such a great place, the food is incredible!
This place is awesome! The food was amazing. The service was 1st class. Will definitely come back on our next trip to DC!!!
I love how their menu service is fast, "private" and convenient! (Easy to "split the bill"). The place is a diamond in the rough.  #HotSake🍶

Probably one of the worst ordering for pickup experiences I've ever had. They use ChowNow to place pickup orders. ChowNow was not able to get in touch with the restaurant. I ended up getting charged for an order I didn't receive. I had to call ChowNow and Sushi Hachi to coordinate my order all on my own. And when I made plans to pick the order up the next day, they were clueless. Here's a tip for sushi hachi-Don't use an online ordering service if you are unresponsive and don't have access to a phone line. Horrible experience.  Update: I sent Sushi Hachi an email to reply to their response, but they did not reply. Crickets...Why even bother?

From the first moment  you enter this restaurant  team give you an agreeable feeling. Very congenial stuff, it is a happy place to go out with friends or with your date. enjoyable  cooking, creative  chef, decent  cost and courteous  service. Highly recommended.

I have had my favorite sushi spots in DC for years— but the first time I tried Sushi Hachi all that changed. Their sushi is absolutely delicious and perfectly made every time. The Capitol Roll is amazing!! Their food is reasonably priced and consistent, I usually order once a week!
Very good food. The napkins were innovative. We had Cali roll, spicy tuna and crunchy shrimp. Will definitely go back.

Got a huge order to go, picked it up and drive to our destination to eat, only to open the bag and find that we were provided no chopsticks or silverware or any kind, no sauces of any kind and no wasabi. What a dumb fail with a huge impact. Waste of my dinner, waste of money and time, and waste of otherwise probably decent sushi.
Great service and ambience! They had super cool napkins on the tables that really added to the experience. The ceviche was especially delicious.
Very accommodating and great food. The "summer" cocktail is the way to go
Meh.  It was fine
Have ordered from here on UberEats a few times, and the fish has been consistently disappointing. Also, they don’t give you fresh ginger or wasabi which sucks.
Great ambience and intimate setting. The food is some of the best and fresh seafood! Staff were very helpful with their recommendations and helped us choose some great sake as well
Low quality sushi! They made everything super sweet. The roll pieces all fell apart.

I meet with friends this lovely place  a lot! This is the best place to pass a nice evening.  I visit this spot routinely. The cooking is fantastic, the staff members are friendly and the prices are fair. I like going in this restaurant to have a decent meal.

Food: It was beautiful. Too beautiful. High quality in taste, and even better presentation. The waguya stone dish was very interesting and a great experience. The cocktails were to die for. Atmosphere: We sat outdoors, it wasn’t too bad. The exterior of the restaurant is very beautiful and gave a lovely modern japanese vibe. Staff: They staff were friendly and very knowledgeable of the food. A great help, and I’m glad this place exists in Maryland. Price: Pricey, but for the quality and presentation, definitely worth it. I would recommend to definitely dine in rather than order take out since the experience isn’t the same.
The sushi bowl was delicious. I took this photo after I ate the tempura and miso soup. The service was great. Thank you Zaya! 😊

Amazing service.  I went when were allowed to go outside and play (lol).  Everything was amazing and the service was top notch.  I had never been to a real sushi place before so for this being my first experience, I was impressed.  I will return here as well as order takeout from here now that I know that they are on GrubHub!
Excellent sushi quality and presentation for takeout. Great pickup situation
Best sushi place ever! Great service!
Best sushi ever!!!
Not as many pieces if sushi I would get if I went into safe way or something. Wasnt that bad.
Ordered from Uber eats, everything was delicious.
Absolutely delicious! Great prices! Amazing service! I would also recommend the Pearl cocktail.
Sushi is amazing . That Capitol roll had me a purchase a total of 5 trays in two days. This my new sushi spot fo show!!
HORRIBLE! I just ordered delivery & rolls had hair on it. No good at all...regardless of the hair! DON’T DO IT!!!!!!

Ordered through Uber Eats.….  Food was okay but I was expecting fresh ginger and not packs.  I also paid $2 extra for extra wasabi and all I got was a dab smh TOTAL.  I might give them a try again but I'm not sure.

One star is too good. Horrible staff, communication and management.  Waited over an hour and a half after app said order was ready before giving up and leaving without food. No one was working the pick up, giving updates on status or cancelling orders when they could not complete. Could not cancel on the app myself. Tried to call the restaurant and saw them decline the call through the window. I'll be charging back.  I was lucky to have the free time on a nice night but I feel bad for the app delivery drivers. Many had to call customers, try to explain the situation, ask the customer to cancel the order and charge back.

Ordered through Grubhub never got the food. Had to cancel it not because I wanted to but becuase neither the driver nor the resturant was responding. Didn't even get to use the first time purchase coupon either, since I used it on order that neve showed up. Im just sad cause I was hungry, anxious, and excited; and was met with only disappoint (partially at the hand of Grubhub, and the other half at the hand of the resturant).
Delicious soups. Fresh sushi 🍣

Came here today for lunch. Very cute place with a bit of a contemporary rustic motif (with high ceilings and exposed brick along one side of the rectangular restaurant).  We had the Prime Beef to start (similar to wagyu) and is accompanied by a superheated rock so you can prepare it to your liking table side. The beef was good - not A5 wagyu level, but definitely top filet or sirloin - and served with three condiments which we loved. The truffle salt is AMAZING. I've had truffle salts before but this is done with a good amount of truffle oil flavor. The other two sauces are also very good, though I think I preferred the steak as-is after salting it on both sides with the truffle salt.  We also got the Cucumber Avocado Roll, Spicy Tuna, and Capitol (specialty) rolls (one of each). I liked the Capitol roll best but not giving 5 stars because I didn't think the sushi was any better than average - and the Capitol roll (which is tempura) was just barely warm when it was served.  Overall great experience and will return for the prime beef, though we may skip the sushi next time.
Good food and drinks. Nice atmosphere.
Sushi was very delicious and the staff was knowledgeable and helpful with the menu. The snapper ceviche was great and the volcano roll was very tasty. Will definitely be coming back soon.
The staff was kind, attentive & the sushi was of good quality. Overall, an enjoyable experience!
Good food
Sushi is the bomb and happy our is very affordable
Good Sushi...Nooshi was packed this was more then i expected. Great spot tucked away. The atmosphere is awesome staff is ultra cool and know the menu very well.

My favorite sushi place in DC- great, high quality rolls, affordable prices, and nice ambiance and service!  I've only ordered their sushi rolls, so I can't speak to their other dishes (which look great also). Their rolls are $6-7 for 6 pieces for their classic rolls and 4 pieces for their speciality rolls. They have all the classics- spicy tuna/salmon, tuna/salmon avocado, eel, yellowtail, crunchy shrimp tempura. My favorites are the eel and yellowtail; the yellowtail roll has a really fresh jalapeno pico de gallo on top. I also really love their Hachi and Dragon speciality rolls!  Service was great and the ambiance was very clean and nice. Would highly highly recommend checking Sushi Hachi our for some great sushi and Japanese food :)

Kara-age was very oily and not crispy. Never had a leaner "fatty tuna." Maki Rolls were handmade but just ok. One piece of the Prime Beef Nigiri was chewy, the second one was good.  Nice interior, quick service and good presentation of the food.
Least fatty "fatty tuna" I've ever had. Salmon avocado roll was okay but I've had better from grocery stores. Prime beef nigiri was very chewy but tasty.  Service was good and prompt.
(Translated by Google) Very rich  (Original) Muy rico

I ordered to go so maybe that effects what I got, but it shouldn't.  Chirashi bowl was disappointing. Portion size was kind of a joke for the price. Fish cuts were tiny. The salmon was sliced so thin you could see the color from the garnish through it.  Fish quality was good which is the only reason I didn't give 1 star.  Torai down the street is a way better option.
Lovely gustatory experience, reasonable prices

My younger cousin and I were looking for sushi while we were in town today. When we walked in; a man who works there did not acknowledge us. We arrived a little after 2 pm and it was only a table of 4 who was seated. We stood there for about 2 minutes. Even though he was chatting with a customer; it was very clear that we were not welcomed there. No hello, wait just a second, or someone will be right with you. We were treated like invisible brown people. My cousin and I walked out. We will not pour our money into people who can't show respect that we even exist.

This restaurant is my favored. I visit plenty of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The team is very affectionate and the food they cook is so flavorful. I would always prefer to have a decent dinner in this place. I highly recommend this place.
This is the best sushi in DC.  Service is great. Ambiance is great. Everything is great.

Wow horrible place The fish was salted to cover that it was not fresh Super small portions The Uni was old and bitter My daughter had to spit out one sweet shrimp that was under the other two served The fish is served over ice so you are eating frozen cold fish The rolls super small and average Went to this place because of the reviews Not sure who is writing the reviews 150 dollars and I was better off eating a poke bowl Don’t waste your money you will be disappointed and hungry later
Amazing sushi. Happy hour select is ok!

Excited to see a classy new sushi joint on the hill! This would be a good place for a date but do check out the menu in advance as the options are pretty limited.  I arrived after 2:30pm when many restaurant kitchens are closed. These guys stay open all day and the place was as empty as you would expect. Waitress seated me, poured some water and answered a few questions. I ordered a green tea, the chicken karage and spicy tuna sushi then ended with matcha green tea ice cream. My bill was $33 including a 20% tip.  The spicy sushi was ok - not very flavorful but it was fresh and pleasant with ripe avocado and good, sticky rice. The chicken karage is fried in a light flour batter and frankly would have been better in a panko crumb but hey maybe that is how karages are made everywhere?! The thick creamy sauce combined with the oil from the fried chicken was a little much for me. Of course, I still had dessert.  The green tea ice cream comes with three scoops and it’s really creamy, not bitter like matcha can be. This is that rare opportunity when eating the Maraschino cherry makes sense.  Enjoy the easy listening versions of great metal and funk classics that they play in the background here. Thriller, Daddy Cool, Sweet Child O Mine, Live N Let Die and more sung breathily by a very sweet sounding young lady supported by a cast of pan pipes and synthesizers. Wow.
Sushi was outstanding. We kept ordering more.

Really good food. We all enjoyed all of the various rolls and appetizers. They have 2 different combos available, which include an assortment of items at a great value. Lots of sake and other drink options as well

A rare dining gem in SE DC; you can taste the quality of the ingredients. The agedashi tofu is melt-in-your-mouth goodness. The chirashi features an excellent variety of fish, including amberjack, yellowtail, and sea eel.
I had a lovely dinner here. I was visiting from out of state and the prices were very good. The quality of food reminded me of my recent trip to Japan.
I can't believe the quality of this place. Prices are nice and the menu options are all great. I love it. Will return. And often!

Sushi Hachi is one of my favorite spots in DC and I highly recommend it whether you're walking by with friends and stop impromptu or make a reservation for date in advance. The sushi is super fresh and the menu has more than just sushi on it if you're looking for non-fish options.  When I worked in Arlington, I practically lived at Sushi Rock, which is a sibling restaurant to Hachi. Sushi Hachi is like Sushi Rock's older more traditional - but still cool - sibling. Serving authentic sushi with an innovative approach, Hachi is the perfect spot for date night or a night out with friends in Eastern Market. Diners can order a variety of dishes a la carte or the Omakase, which I highly recommend!  Service at Sushi Hachi has always been good when I've been, super friendly and accommodating. - ✨&e Tip: Keep an eye on @GiltCity DC's deals, sometimes they offer the Omakase at Sushi Hachi for an incredible price!

I read about this place and went on a weekday. It was not super busy, but we had a reservation. The ambience was very good and we were impressed by the technique to wash hands with wet tissue. It’s a small white cylinder and the moment u put it in water it becomes a tissue, this was fun.  Coming to the food, the fish here was delicious and hot stone grill beef as well. It’s a must try experience. I would recommend Chu Taro and Tuna. If you want to try multiple types of fishes try the chef tasting platter(sufficient for one person). You will not be disappointed. But it’s a bit pricy though. Overall a great experience. And it’s definitely worth a try.
The hot stone is really nice !
Great sushi. Chirashi bowl very tasty. Service responsive.  Great ambiance.
Great service. Good food. Walk to the Navy Yard.
It's ok.... not the best or the worst

This is one of our favorite places in the neighborhood. The Nigiri and Sashimi are the stars - incredibly fresh and interesting options. The Uni, Toro, and Sea Bass are superb. This isn't your standard sushi place with a thousand roll options - the menu is relatively short but it ensures most everything shines. Service is excellent and it has a good sake and cocktail program.
GOOD SUSHI! This place is not cheap but the sushi is good. They need an Omakase on the menu.

I would give them 5 stars but they recently changed the menu and took futomaki off the menu, they had the best futomaki I ever had in DC, (and I’m a picky eater) me and my boyfriend ate it almost every other day over the summer! I hope they bring it back soon!

Tried this restaurant because I couldn't get a reservation for another restaurant I wanted to try. I am so happy this happened😁 The food and service was amazing!!! I will certainly come again, thank you!
Excellent place to eat some food when in a rush. The customer service is fast, pricing is convenient, awesome atmosphere. Keep up the good work

For me the most important in a sushi place is the sushi taste and freshness, this place looks nice but the sushi tasted like grocery store sushi, nothing special. They need to  concentrate on their food more

We enjoy hanging out. Yesterday we  visited this superb place which friends told us about. We had a delightful experience there with very good cooking and an efficient team and  a professional  chef. We  added this place in our list  and we will surely come back very soon.  Highly recommended.
This place is worth a try. They serve big portions for reasonable prices. Always well organized and with excellent atmosphere. Would recommend to others.
From a non sushi expert- this was delicious! Such a cute little restaurant at the end tail of Eastern market. The restaurant is beautiful and the staff is friendly.

Quite impressed with this restaurant. After being let down through the week with other sushi places, this establishment came as a pleasant surprise.  The dishes were great and the service was phenomenal.
Best miso soup ever, reasonably priced sushi, great staff, and expeditious service...Will place high on my list of favorite places...

Meh food, small portions, and high prices.  Apparently, they just updated their menu.  Their “ceviche” was basically a corn-tomato-onion mixture with a few 1 cm chunks of fish.  Their Unagi nigiri was tiny and did not taste fresh.  Their spicy tuna hand roll was 80% rice with the tiniest bit of minced tuna in the middle. Flavorless.  After eating there, I understand why the place was only a quarter full. I won’t be going back. There are plenty of wonderful sushi places in DC, and this isn’t one of them.
Trendy Japanese fusion fare with excellent quality sashimi.  Try the wagyu beef and unique tomato based soup.

I live in the Salisbury area and I travel to dc just for this place. They have the best sushi i have ever tasted. Everything, even down to the rice is perfection. It's so posh and wonderful. I wish I could give it more than 5 stars.
Very good quality and affordable sushi. I was surprised by the pricing compared to its quality. The service and the environment are also very nice. Definitely recommends this place!

The sushi was delicious! I got the nigiri course and it was good. The only mess up was, they almost gave me the same piece of sushi twice (since each piece is supposed to be different), but I told them and they kindly replace the similar piece. Also, they took everyone's chopsticks before the last roll was served. I think my server is just into cleaning, Also, not that bad since it is sushi, and traditionally one should be eating with their hand.

I was pretty disappointed with the food. Ordered some sashimi, nigiri sushi, rolls and chirashi. The fish doesn't taste fresh,rice was terrible and the rolls feels like it was made early. Things in the rolls look unappetizing,mushy and it doesn't taste good. But, I have to give star to presentation ,ambiance and our attentive waitress, they're good ! Pricewise,it's on the higher end, but maybe that's standard in DC, but I don't think it's worth it.

Absolutely the best sushi I have ever had. The multi-course dinners are a very good option and definitely did not disappoint. Service was also top notch. I will now have tough time since eating at Hachi is for sushi what driving a Tesla is for cars. I am seriously considering moving to DC just so I can eat here every week.
Phenomenal sushi. Get the prix fix. It will not disappoint.
The food was excellent and the service was good.
A little pricey
The service and the food was excellent. Our waitress was fast and attentive. The atmosphere was nearly perfect.
Pretty reasonable prices and really good!

Lovely setting, really friendly staff who let us try Shochu before buying, and an affordable menu however we were quite disappointed by the speed of the service. We went for the omakase menu and we have no idea if it was even good or not because they brought the dishes out so fast that we ended up so full up about half way through. We kept a hold of our dishes and would be only half way through before the next dish would be set in front of us, they didn’t wait for us to have finished. By the time it got to the Wagyu beef I couldn’t even have one bite. It took them about 50 minutes to serve us 7 courses which didn’t make for a relaxing evening. Once or twice I was going to ask for more time but I’d look up for someones attention and they’d be there with our next course already.  The first couple of dishes were nice, the tuna on the sashimi was cut incredibly thin to the point mine tore in two when picking it up with chopsticks.  I think I would go back and be sure to tell them to slow down next time, I also might not go for the omakase and just order when I’m ready.

This place is incredibly special. From the outstanding service to the amazing food. My husband and I will drive more than one hour to come here all the time. The manager and every single one of the servers are so personable and amazing to get to know. And the food, wow!! That’s all I can say. I wish we could eat here every day!!!
Food was great and our server was fantastic. Sebastian's service was impeccable.
Great food, but quite noisy.

Sitting here now. Nice atmosphere very good service. The sushi however is really unusual in presentation and honestly not very good. The fish is very mushy, no fresh taste. Was expecting great sushi and was disappointed.

Came to Sushi Hachi after hearing good reviews about it. Since I came with a friend who eats basic sushi, wasn't able to experience the full sushi experience. Will definitely have to come back and order the sashimi I would normally order to get a better idea of the flavors of the sushi. Ordered the Chicken Kara-age, Wagyu Beef, Uni Roll with Quail Egg, and Futomaki Roll.  The good: Chicken Kara-age was good, as the chicken was tender while the batter was pretty crispy and flavorful. The Waygu Beef was good, and it had a nice taste with the sauce it was covered with. The Uni Roll and Quail Egg was quite delicious, but you have to request for a Quail Egg. Surprisingly, the Futomaki Roll was good. This is a roll I would rarely order because there's no fish in it, but I enjoyed it.  The bad: Wasn't anything wrong with the place, but it may be difficult to find parking since they only have street parking available.  Overall, the food was delicious, but I will have to return to access how the sushi is at this restaurant since I didn't really have the opportunity except for the Uni.
Great atmosphere, prices, food and service.  The tempura was a little bland but everything else was great.

What a wonderful place. Great atmosphere. Excellent staff. Above average food. Bartender was very nice and even gave us a free after dinner drink. Portions are great. The fresh water eel is to die for. Their take on creme brulee is delicious, a must try!
Very good sushi, nice environment. Will definitely be back. I recommend the blue crab roll. Delicious !

We were seated promptly despite being 11 minutes late to our reservation. Our server was attentive and the service provided was prompt. The sashimi and rolls served were exceptional. There is a very romantic and yet very relaxed ambiance to this establishment. Highly recommend dining here!
Presentation of food, quality of sushi and meat was wonderful. Crowded with serving staffs around the kitchen area was a little down side.

Food was very tasty good flavors. But my yellow tail roll had the spicy seasoning unevenly distributed so that the center pieces were way too spicy. And I like spicy food.  More importantly, they only serve bluefin tuna as a tuna option. This is extremely unsustainable. They don't have any clear information on the origin of their seafood. Was very disappointed in the lack of awareness of the sustainability issues associated with seafood.
Good sushi, very interesting/original drinks...
Just an unbelievable meal. Tried to capture the whole omakase experience here but still missed a couple dishes! An incredible value for the journey you go through. Will 100% be back.
Great service.  Great menu!  I love this place.

It's always a treat when I get the chance to come to Sushi Hachi. For one reason or another, it’s been a while since my last visit here.  Anyway, my wife and I came here this past weekend and the service and food are still amazing. We always try something new every time we come back. We tried several different beverages including the dreams come true, sexy lip, gentleman, Pearl, and the summer. All very different, but all very good...as well as strong.  For food, we tried the chicken-kara-age, grilled octopus too, chefs selection, blue crab tuna tartare, kimpachi crudo, roasted squash soap, mini chirashi sushi, octopus croquettes, ishiyaki waygu and lastly the Hachi charashi Sushi. Honestly, everything was amazing!  The restaurant itself is always kept clean and well maintained. Our server brought our food out to us quickly and correctly.  Their is street parking outside but it can sometimes be a pain to find someplace to park. Otherwise another great dinner at Sushi Hachi!
Delicious date night dinner at the bar! Two of us shared the nigiri special. Made for one, but plenty for two with drinks. Took us too long to try it. Will be back.
I like their ambiance, the service was nice but my server didn't offer me any Wasabi even we ordered too much sushi, they don't serve with wasabi. Food is good for sushi restaurant in town.

This was probably the most authentic sushi I've ever had. The spicy tuna and yellowfish rolls were delicious. My husband ordered the 7 course meal that the chef recommended and enjoyed every course. It was a great value for the quantity and quality of the food as well as the experience.
Some of the best sushi in the DC area
Awesome food!
amazing sushi
Very nice environment with great food and people!
Nice experience,  great food
Very tasty and immaculately presented courses. The omakase menu is delightful.
A hidden gem. Affordable, high quality, and delicious. Get the fatty tuna!
Great spot! Awesome sushi, great service and nice set up and atmosphere. Loved our dinner here and can’t wait to come back.
Most beautiful take out containers and packaging.
7 course meal that brought joy to fine dining.
The food here was amazing. I ordered the omakase and every step of the meal was cooked perfectly. There was a amazing balance of sushi, nigiri, of soft and chewy, and of crisp and light items.
Not a lot of food for the price.

My husband and I had the 7 course meal and it was pretty good. A mix of flavors and options so if you want straight sushi do not get this option. The tables filled up quickly so if you don't have a reservation get there early if you want a table, early being anytime before 6pm during the week at least. The cocktails are very unique but tasty and the sake is good.
Perfect dinner choice,!!!
Amazing food! Get the omakase meal for a little bit of everything!

We had a really nice time here! Despite arriving about 10min late for our reservation, the host was kind and welcoming and we were seated promptly. The interior is super cute and creates a nice upscale vibe. This is a great spot for a date. The kitchen takes great care in plating beautiful dishes, and the fish is fresh and delicious. For such high quality food, the prices are very reasonable!
The service is excellent and always a stellar meal. My go to spot for sushi in DC.
Fantastic, carefully curated sushi in a crisp, modern setting. The 12-piece nigiri experience is served as four courses plus miso and edamame, and every piece was stunning. Can't wait to go back!
Fresh, well presented, variety of proposed menu is very interesting.

We ate at the bar, and our service was provided by Namuun - it was excellent in every aspect. Courteous, prompt, personalized attention - continuing throughout our meal without being intrusive. For example, her suggestions and clarifications on the composition and preparation of the evening's dishes, tactful guidance on dining customs, and assurance that our meal was presented in an appropriate order of dishes. We were certain she either owned or managed the restaurant. The food was wonderful - classic elements reassembled delicious combinations, with artful presentation. Our dining included the Miso soup of the day, edamame, wagyu beef Hachi style, grilled octopus / seaweed / spicy tuna, ginger,, a sushi roll and fresh draft Kirin beer.  The restaurant is fresh, classy but relaxed, with calming retro orchestral music.  It's worth your while to travel down 8th street to Sushi Hachi.

Dessert (pictured) was excellent, we had the shaved ice and also represents what I said above. Beautiful presentation on all dishes.  Service: We had Nomon serving my wife and I this night. She was an absolute delight and was one of the best and most friendly waitresses we have ever had. The rest of the staff was very attentive and friendly as well.  Overall, as I said before, highly recommended. We will certainly come back if in this part of town again.

Given the positive reviews, I had such great hopes for this place. Unfortunately I left very disappointed.  Positives: the food was terrific. I ordered omakase and the chef did a good job providing a diversity of dishes that all complemented each other. The fish was fresh and flavorful. Ambiance was a little loud but otherwise enjoyable.  Negatives: SERVICE, SERVICE, SERVICE. Although we had a 7pm reservation, we were left waiting for 15 minutes, until 715, despite seeing several open tables. This would ordinarily not bother me, but I witnessed several parties of the same size (2 people) who came after us were seated before we were. I was told twice that they were cleaning our table as we waited, no apology.  After being seated, everything was going smoothly until the smoked sashimi dish. We finished the course and waited 20 minutes until I had to flag a waitress that we hadn't receive our next course. She skipped the nigiri dish and brought out the soup. I informed her that the dishes were out of order, received no apology, she took back the soup, we waited another 10 minutes, finally got the nigiri, then she brought out a soup that was cold, which I assume was the original dish brought out by mistake... again no apology.  I'm usually very understanding when mixups happen but this was over the top. I won't be going back, which is a shame because the good itself was excellent and I love supporting new restaurant.

Ok, let's start with the good. Food quality is excellent, location is nice. Management comp'd drinks for issues.  The bad: almost everything else. We were seated 45 minutes after our reservation. Service was ABYSMAL. Dishes were forgotten, came out without sauces, sushi missing accompanying ginger, hot food occasionally lukewarm. Had to get up and ask for water or drink refills. Took about 2.5 hours for our 7-person party. Service issues seemed equally split between the kitchen and the servers.  Management apologized and comp'd our (rather significant) bar tab, but there are some serious issues at this place. Beware.

Hachi easily qualifies as one of the top 5 sushi places in DC.     Quality of fish here is noticeably a cut above other places, with silky toro, firm salmon, unctuous ankimo, all served with a mix of innovation but firmly grounded in traditional Japanese.  Toro handroll (classic traditional) was generous and amazing, timed to come out with the nori still crispy, and overall on par with top end places in NYC and SF.  A crab-truffle handroll (modern) was very good as well, with the crab marrying well with the truffle oil.  A special plug for the Chirashi, which was *very* generous with the fish, and artfully arranged (see picture).  The ikura was very freshly made, with tiny pearls of salmon egg that popped with briney flavor (instead of tough flabby skin that many other places have).  VERY happy to finally have a legit, upscale (non-BS-fusiony) Japanese place on Barracks Row that focuses on high end sushi/sashimi with a slight inventive flair.
This place is incredible— food, service, ambiance— everything. Definitely will be back.
